y experiences of the film economy in New Orleans, Louisiana-a city that has twice pursued the goal of becoming a movie production capital. From the silent era to today's Hollywood South, Vicki Mayer explains that the aura of a film economy is inseparable from a prevailing sense of home, even as it changes that place irrevocably.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture industryzLouisianazNew Orleans. 7aPERFORMING ARTS / Film & Video / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066755440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780520967175?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967175zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967175/original  a978-3-11-066755-4 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA